==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mosstrooper
<hw>Moss"troop`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Moss</ets>
+ <ets>trooper</ets>.]</ety> <def>One of a class of marauders or bandits
that formerly infested the border country between England and Scotland;
-- so called in allusion to the <xex>mossy</xex> or boggy character of
much of the border country.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mossy</ent>⟦br⟧
